[Are there any data supporting the cost effectiveness of this exercise?
Might the time and money be better spent on establishing a good active
surveillance system that would detect suspect cases earlier? This could be
combined with the preparation of educational materials for people returning
from the infected areas with advice to seek medical attention if they
developed symptoms, along with sensitizing the health care personnel to
include cholera in the differential diagnosis of gastroenteritis as well as
the need for immediate reporting of suspect cases. - MPP
